Spot ETFs provide a way for investors to invest in Bitcoin through traditional brokerage accounts similar to buying stocks. They are designed to track the price of Bitcoin closely and provide a convenient and regulated way for investors to participate in the cryptocurency market

Unlike futures-based ETFs which derive their value from Bitcoin futures contracts a spot ETF holds physical Bitcoin. This means that the ETF owns the actual Bitcoin and seeks to reflect its market price.
A Bitcoin spot ETF or Exchange-Traded Fund is a financial product that allows investors to gain exposure to the price movements of Bitcoin without actually owning the cryptocurrency itself.
